      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Lao et al.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T071539Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T071539Z">
        <seg>Лао и др. </seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>List of reviewed articles by year</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T042629Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T042629Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>More details about research paper recommender system evaluation methods follow in Sect.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T055132Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T055132Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>More than one-third (36 %) had 10 or more pages (Fig. 2).</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043253Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043253Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Nevertheless, these approaches to represent a concept are still vague and leave room for speculation on how recommendations are calculated.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T053109Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T053109Z">
        <seg>Методики вычисления интереса в них варьируются.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Numbers are based on our literature search.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T042433Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T042433Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Of course, users require recommendations specific to their fields of research [117].</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T054836Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T054836Z">
        <seg>При этом оба типа пользователей нуждаются в рекомендациях.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Of the 96 research-paper recommendation approaches presented in 185 articles, 62 approaches were chosen for an in-depth analysis, presented in 127 articles [1–127].</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043503Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043503Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>One example of an article outside of the research scope was ‘Research Paper Recommender Systems—A Subspace Clustering Approach’ [130].</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043532Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043532Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Only eleven approaches applied collaborative filtering, and none of them successfully used explicit ratings.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T065245Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T065245Z">
        <seg>Только в одиннадцати РС применяется коллаборативная фильтрация, и ни в одном из них не удалось успешно использовать явные рейтинги.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Other approaches modeled their users as graphs, as lists with topics that were assigned through machine learning, or as ACM classification hierarchies.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T064930Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T064930Z">
        <seg>Другие подходы моделируют своих пользователей при помощи графов и списков тем, назначенных им в результате машинного обучения, или в виде иерархий на основе классификаторов АСМ.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Other recommendation concepts included stereotyping, item-centric recommendations, and hybrid recommendations.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T035515Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T035515Z">
        <seg>Другие подходы к построению рекомендаций включают стереотипирование, гибридные методы и др.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Our relevance judgment made use of the title and the abstract if the title alone did not indicate a recognizable relevance to research-paper recommender systems.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043109Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043109Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Our review revealed some shortcomings of the current research.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T040015Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T040015Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Overall, the reviewed articles were comprehensive, with a median page count of eight.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043243Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043243Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Page count of reviewed articles
Citation counts follow a typical power–law distribution: a few articles gained many citations (the maximum was 528 citations for [43]) and many articles had few citations, see Fig. 3.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043301Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043301Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Percentage of different article types reviewed
https://static-content.springer.com/image/art%3A10.1007%2Fs00799-015-0156-0/MediaObjects/799_2015_156_Fig2_HTML.gif
Fig. 2</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043258Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043258Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Pohl et al.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T071044Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T071044Z">
        <seg>Пол и др</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Research-paper recommender systems: a literature survey</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T051038Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T034619Z">
        <seg>Исследование рекомендательных систем: обзор литературы (http://docear.org/papers/Research%20Paper%20Recommender%20Systems%20--%20A%20Literature%20Survey%20(preprint).pdf)</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Since then, at least 216 articles relating to 120 research-paper recommendation approaches were published [2–217].</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T042258Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T042258Z">
        <seg>(216 статей с тех пор)</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Six of the reviewed approaches were co-occurrence based.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T070612Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T070612Z">
        <seg>Шесть из рассмотренных подходов основывались на анализе совместного появления (сочетаемости, co-occurrence).</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Some graphs included authors, users/customers, venues, genes and proteins, and publishing years of the papers.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T071530Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T071530Z">
        <seg>Некоторые графы включают авторов, пользователей/клиентов, [площадки venues], гены и белки, и годы публикации документов.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Some recommender systems also use two or more recommendation approaches: CiteULike, a service for discovering and managing scholarly references, lets their users choose between two approaches [14, 17], and Docear randomly selects one of three approaches each time users request recommendations [7].</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T054257Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T054257Z">
        <seg>(в статье рассмотрены также системы, реализующие несколько подходов одновременно.)</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Some researchers have reservations about using Google Scholar as source for citation counts [218–220], but the numbers can give a rough idea of a paper’s popularity.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043340Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043340Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Some used n-grams, or topics based on LDA.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T060219Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T060219Z">
        <seg>Некоторые использовуют N-граммы, или темы на основе LDA.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Sometimes content-based filtering performed better than collaborative filtering and sometimes it performed worse.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T040306Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T040252Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Stefan Langer</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T034658Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T034658Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Such graphs typically included papers that were connected via citations.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T071403Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T071403Z">
        <seg>Эти графы обычно включают документы, для которых обнаружены общие цитаты.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>TF-IDF was the most frequently applied weighting scheme.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T035923Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T035923Z">
        <seg>Наиболее часто применяемая здесь схема взвешивания - TF-IDF.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Table 2</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043256Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043256Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Ten recommendation approaches built graphs to generate recommendations.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T071314Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T071314Z">
        <seg>Десять подходов к РС строили графы для создания рекомендаций.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The amount of literature and approaches represents a problem for new researchers: they do not know which of the articles are most relevant, and which recommendation approaches are most promising.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T042320Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T042320Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The articles consisted primarily of peer-reviewed conference papers (59 %), journal articles (16 %), pre-prints (5 %), and other documents such as presentations and web pages (15 %).</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T055847Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T055847Z">
        <seg>Статьи состояли в основном из рецензируемых трудах конференций (59 %), журнальные статьи (16 %), препринтов (5 %) и других документов, таких как презентации и веб-страниц (15 %).</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The authors reported reasonable performance of the stereotype approach with click-through rates (CTR) around 4 % while the CBF approach achieves CTRs around 6 %.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T070217Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T070217Z">
        <seg>Авторы получили приемлемые показатели для этого подхода через коэффициент кликабельности (CTR) (около 4%), в то время как подход CBF достигал примерно 6 %.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The content-based filtering approaches mainly utilized papers that the users had authored, tagged, browsed, or downloaded.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T035721Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T035721Z">
        <seg>Контент-фильтрация в основном использует информацию о торм, какие товары и услуги заказывают потребители.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The few existing literature surveys in the field [186–188] cover just a fraction of the articles, or focus on selected aspects, such as recommender-system evaluation [190].</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T042357Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T042357Z">
        <seg>(В статьях 186-188 - литобзоры)</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The few existing literature surveys in this field cover only a fraction of these articles, which is why we conducted a comprehensive survey of research-paper recommender systems.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T055941Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T055934Z">
        <seg>Существующие обзоры литературы в этой области охватывают лишь малую часть этих статей, поэтому мы провели комплексное обследование таких систем.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The goal of this search was to identify the overall number of articles published in 2013; see Fig. 1.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043557Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043557Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The higher the proximity of two references within a paper, the more related they are assumed to be.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T071035Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T071035Z">
        <seg>Предположено, что чем выше близость двух ссылок в статье, тем более релевантными они являются.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The main problem of collaborative filtering for research papers seems to be scarcity.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T065725Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T065725Z">
        <seg>Главная проблема совместной фильтрации для научных работ, кажется, дефицит информации.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The mean citation count was 30, and median was seven.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043307Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043307Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The most popular model to store item representations was the Vector Space Model.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T060244Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T060244Z">
        <seg>Самая популярная модель для хранения представления элемента - модель векторного пространства.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The needs of users vary.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T054639Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T054639Z">
        <seg>Потребности пользователей меняются.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The objective of a recommender system from a broad perspective is to provide “good” [224] and “useful” [225] recommendations that make users “happy” [226] by satisfying user needs [87].</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T054630Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T054630Z">
        <seg>Цель РС в широком смысле - это обеспечить “хорошие” [224] и “полезные” [225] рекомендации, которые делают пользователи “счастливым” [226] путем удовлетворения его потребностей [87].</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The remaining 185 articles consist of peer-reviewed conference articles (59 %), journal articles (16 %), pre-prints (5 %), and other formats such as Ph.D.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043232Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043232Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The review included an analysis of which evaluation methods were applied (e.g., user-studies or offline evaluations), which evaluation metrics were used (e.g., precision or recall), how many participants the user studies had, and how strongly datasets were pruned.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043458Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043458Z">
        <seg>(интересует измерения качества результатам)</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The review revealed the following information.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T060002Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T060002Z">
        <seg>В ходе обзора выявлена следующая информация.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The reviewed approaches extracted text from the title, abstract, header, introduction, foreword, author-provided keywords, bibliography, body text, social tags, and citation context.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T065149Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T065149Z">
        <seg>В рассмотренных подходах тексты извлекаются из заглавий, аннотаций, заголовков, введения, предисловия, предоставленных автором ключевых слов, библиографии, основного текста, социальных тегов и цитирований контекста.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The title appears relevant for this survey, but the article presents a collaborative filtering approach that is not intended for recommender systems for research papers.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043541Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043541Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>The “recommendation scenario” describes the entire setting of a recommender system, including the recommender system and the recommendation environment, i.e., the domain and user characteristics.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T054436Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T054436Z">
        <seg>“Сценарий построения рекомендации” описывает всю настройку РС, в том числе ИС и ее окружение, т.е. предметную область продукта или услуги, а также характеристики пользователя.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Therefore, our review concentrates on the two subsets of the 217 articles: the 185 articles identified during the first round of the literature search, and the 127 articles that we chose for an in-depth review.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043605Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043605Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>These approaches are quite different, but are each consistent with the central idea of CF.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T053009Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T053009Z">
        <seg>Эти подходы совершенно разные, но каждый соответствует классу CF.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>These major academic services include the academic search engines CiteSeer(x),2Google Scholar (Scholar Update),3 and PubMed;4 the social network ResearchGate;5 and the reference managers CiteULike,6Docear,7 and Mendeley.8 While these systems offer recommender systems along with their main services, there are also a few stand-alone recommender systems, namely BibTip,9bX,10RefSeer,11TheAdvisor12 and an experimental system called Sarkanto.13
The first literature search was conducted in June 2013 and found 188 relevant articles [1–188].</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043202Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043202Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>They were based on strongly pruned datasets, few participants in user studies, or did not use appropriate baselines.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T040452Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T040452Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>This means that for a particular recommendation approach there might be several algorithms.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T053712Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T053712Z">
        <seg>Это означает, что для каждой практической реализации существует несколько алгоритмов.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Three approaches analyzed how often papers were co-viewed during a browsing session: whenever users browsed a paper, the system recommended those papers that had frequently been co-viewed with the browsed paper in the past.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T070845Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T070845Z">
        <seg>В трех подходах анализировалось частота совместного просмотра документа во течение сеанса [просмотра]: в процессе просмотра пользователем статьи, система рекомендует к просмотру документы, которые часто совместно просматривались в прошлом.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Three of the 188 articles were literature surveys [186–188], which were ignored in our survey.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043216Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043216Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Thus, they do not provide an overview of the research field, or identify the most promising approaches.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T042407Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T042407Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>To differentiate how specific the idea is, we distinguish between recommendation classes, approaches, algorithms, and implementations (Fig. 4).</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T044017Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T044017Z">
        <seg>Каждый конкретный экземпляр (идея) РС классифицируется по [классам рекомендаций], подходам, алгоритмам и [реализациям] (Рис. 4). </seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>To identify relevant literature for our survey, we conducted a literature search on Google Scholar, ACM Digital Library,Springer Link, and ScienceDirect.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043049Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043049Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Vellino compared implicit ratings on Mendeley (research papers) and Netflix (movies), and found that scarcity on Mendeley differs from Netflix by a magnitude of three.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T065857Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T065857Z">
        <seg>Vellino сравнил неявные оценоки на Mendeley (научные статьи) и Netflix (фильмы), и обнаружил, что дефицит на Mendeley отличается от Netflix в [3 раза, в степени 3 ии ж 1000 раз].</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We also excluded articles that could not be clearly interpreted due to grammar and language use, or when they were outside of the scope (even if the article’s title suggested relevance to research-paper recommender systems).</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043525Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043525Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We also identified a lack of authority and long-term research interest in the field: 73 % of the authors published no more than one paper on research-paper recommender systems, and there was little cooperation among different co-author groups.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T041937Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T041937Z">
        <seg>Выявлен факт того, что в долгосрочной перспективе научный интерес в этой области не представлен: 73 % авторов написали только одну статью на тему  рекомендательных систем, кроме того, сотрудничества между различными исследовательскими группами не наблюдается.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We chose these 62 approaches, because we classified the remaining 34 approaches, i.e., 58 articles, as not sufficiently related to ‘research-paper recommender systems’ [128–185].</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043506Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043506Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We classified articles as insufficiently related if they provided no evaluation, or if their approach did not differ significantly from that of previous authors.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043513Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043513Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We concluded that several actions could improve the research landscape: developing a common evaluation framework, agreement on the information to include in research papers, a stronger focus on non-accuracy aspects and user modeling, a platform for researchers to exchange information, and an open-source framework that bundles the available recommendation approaches.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T042101Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T042101Z">
        <seg>Предложено создать общую открытую программную платформу для ведения исследований в этой области.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We define a “recommendation class” as the least specific idea, namely a broad concept that broadly describes how recommendations might be given.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T051930Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T051930Z">
        <seg>Класс рекомендации - это фундаментальная основа некоторого подхода, которая в целом описывает метод вычисления рекомендации.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We examined the bibliography of each article.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043116Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043116Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We expanded our search to websites, blogs, patents, and presentations on major academic recommender systems.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043151Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043151Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We found that more than half of the recommendation approaches applied content-based filtering (55 %).</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T035043Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T035043Z">
        <seg>Больше половины подходов относятся к фильтрации содержания (55 %) [ссылка на статью-обзор].</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We identified three potential reasons for the ambiguity of the results.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T040528Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T040335Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We reviewed the 185 articles, which contained information on 96 research-paper recommendation approaches [1–185].</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043347Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043347Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We reviewed these articles and present some descriptive statistics in this paper, as well as a discussion about the major advancements and shortcomings and an overview of the most common recommendation concepts and approaches.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T034919Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T034919Z">
        <seg>Рассматриваются популярные подходы к разработке рекомендательных информационных систем, их достоиства и недостатки.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We searched for [paper | article | citation] [recommender | recommendation] [system | systems] and downloaded all articles that had relevance for research-paper recommender systems.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043057Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043057Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We survey the field of research-paper recommender systems with the goal of enabling researchers and developers to (a) learn about the status-quo of research-paper recommender systems, (b) identify promising fields of research, and (c) motivate the community to solve the most urgent problems that currently hinder the effective use of research-paper recommender systems in practice.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T042952Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T042952Z">
        <seg>Цель статьи - показать исследователям и разработчикам (а) современное состояние предметной области, (б) выявить перспективные направления исследований (C) указать первоочередные задачи, требующие решения.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We then present the survey of the 96 approaches’ evaluations (Sect.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T043614Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T043614Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>We use the terms “performance” and “effectiveness” interchangeably.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T054958Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T054958Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>When we use the term “effectiveness,” we refer to the specific objective the evaluator wanted to measure.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T054952Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T054952Z">
        <seg>Всякий раз как упоминается "эффективность" будет указываться по отношению к какой цели.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>Yang et al.</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T065254Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T065254Z">
        <seg>-</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu>
      <tuv lang="EN-US">
        <seg>compared the effectiveness of co-citations and co-downloads and found that co-downloads are more effective than co-citations only in the first 2 years after a paper was published [110].</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv lang="RU-RU" changeid="eugeneai" changedate="20161212T071236Z" creationid="eugeneai" creationdate="20161212T071236Z">
        <seg>сравнили эффективность со-цитирования и со-загрузку. Оказалось, что совместные загрузки показывают большую эффективность, чем со-цитирование только в первые два года со дня опубликования статьи [110].</seg>
